===Etymology 2===
{{ja-kanjitab|さかい|yomi=k|alt=界:less _ common}}
{{swp|ja:}}

{{IPAchar|/sakapi/}} → {{IPAchar|/sakaɸi/}} → {{IPAchar|/sakahi/}} → {{IPAchar|/sakai/}}

The {{m|ja|連用形|tr=ren'yōkei||continuative or stem form}} of obsolete verb {{m|ja|境う|tr=sakau||to divide, to form a boundary between things}}.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref><ref name="DJR"/>

Some sources<ref name="KDJ"/> further derive the verb as {{der|ja|ojp|sort=さかい|-}} element {{m|ja|境|tr=saka||division, border, boundary}} + auxiliary verb {{m|ja|ふ|tr=fu}} indicating repetition or ongoing state. However, given the semantics, this could also be analyzed as the repetitive or ongoing aspect of {{m+|ojp|-}}-derived verb ''saku'' with an underlying meaning of “to split apart, to separate, to put distance between”, spelled variously as {{ja-r|割く|さく|rom=-}}, {{ja-r|裂く|さく|rom=-}}, {{ja-r|離く|さく|rom=-}}, or {{ja-r|放く|さく|rom=-}}, and cognate with {{ja-r|咲く|さく|to [[bloom]]|pos=from the idea of the blooms splitting open}}, {{ja-r|栄える|さかえる|to [[prosper]]|pos=extended from the ''bloom'' sense}}, and {{ja-r|盛る|さかる|to be in [[prime]] [[condition]], to [[prosper]], to [[flourish]]}}.

